{{Infobox person | name = Gary DeVore | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1941|09|17}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date and age|1997|06|28|1941|09|17}} | death_place = [[Santa Fe, New Mexico]], U.S. | yearsactive = | occupation = Screenwriter }} '''Gary DeVore''' (September 17, 1941 – June 28, 1997) was a [[Hollywood]] [[screenwriter]] best known for ''[[Raw Deal (1986 film)|Raw Deal]]'' and for his bizarre death in 1997.
==Career== Devore began his writing career in the late 1960s on shows like [[Chuck Barris]]' ''[[The Newlywed Game]]'', ''[[The Steve Allen Show]]'', and ''[[Tempo]]''.<ref name="LAT">{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1986-07-17/entertainment/ca-21495_1_gary-devore|title=Production Chief Buys--and Sells--scripts|first=DAVID T.|last=FRIENDLY|date=17 July 1986|publisher=|via=LA Times}}</ref>
=== Screenwriter credits === *''[[The Dogs of War (film)|The Dogs of War]]'' (with [[George Malko]]) (1980) *''[[Backroads]]'' (1981) *''[[Heart of Steel]]'' (TV) (1983) *''[[Running Scared (1986 film)|Running Scared]]'' (with Jimmy Huston) (1986)<ref name="LAT"/> *''[[Raw Deal (1986 film)|Raw Deal]]'' (with [[Norman Wexler]]) (1986)<ref name="LAT"/> *''[[Traxx (film)|Traxx]]'' (also producer) (1988) *''[[CBS Summer Playhouse]]'' ([[The Heat (1988 TV movie)|The Heat]]) (with [[David Debin]]) (TV) (1988) *''[[Showdown in Little Tokyo]]'' (1991) (uncredited) *''[[Passenger 57]]'' (uncredited) (1992) *''[[Pentathlon (film)|Pentathlon]]'' (with William Stadiem and [[Gary T. McDonald]]) (1994) *''[[Time Cop]]'' (uncredited) (1994) *''[[Sudden Death (1995 film)|Sudden Death]]'' (uncredited) (1995) *''[[The Relic (film)|The Relic]]'' (uncredited) (1997)
== Personal life and death == DeVore married the singer [[Maria Cole]] (1969–1978)<ref name="LAT"/> and the actresses [[Sandie Newton]] (1981–1985),<ref name="LAT"/> [[Claudia Christian]] (1988–1992),<ref name="DM"/> and Wendy Devore (1996–1997).
DeVore disappeared in June 1997, while driving at night from [[Santa Fe, New Mexico]] to [[Santa Barbara, California]], prompting an extensive search and media speculation.<ref name="SATZMAN">{{Cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1998/jul/09/news/mn-2218|title=Missing Writer's Body Believed Found|last=SATZMAN|first=DARRELL|date=1998-07-09|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2018-05-10|last2=GLOVER|first2=SCOTT|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> A year later, he and his car were discovered submerged below a bridge over the [[California Aqueduct]] in [[Palmdale, California]].<ref name="SATZMAN"/>
A multimedia project, ''[[The Writer with No Hands]]'', posited that DeVore's death was the result of a US government conspiracy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prettycleverfilms.com/movie-reviews/documentary/hot-docs-2014-writer-hands-2014/ |title=Review: Pretty Clever Films, 16th April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Brown |first=Phil |url=http://dorkshelf.com/2014/04/21/hot-docs-2014-the-writer-with-no-hands/#sthash.O63FxbRL.dpuf |title=Hot Docs 2014: The Writer with No Hands Review |publisher=Dork Shelf |date=April 21, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427084853/http://dorkshelf.com/2014/04/21/hot-docs-2014-the-writer-with-no-hands/ |archivedate=27 April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cineinstyle.com/?tag=gary-devore|title=Gary DeVore – Cine in Style|publisher=}}</ref> It also alleges that the hands autopsied with the body were 200 years old and therefore not DeVore's.<ref name="DM">{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2905392/Hollywood-screenwriter-mysteriously-killed-20-years-ago-working-CIA-hands-sent-autopsy-200-years-old.html|title=EXCLUSIVE: Screenwriter mysteriously killed in 1997 after finishing script that revealed the 'real reason' for US invasion of Panama had been working for the CIA... and both his hands were missing|first1=Mia |last1=De Graaf |first2=Sean |last2=O'Hare|work=[[The Daily Mail]]|date=January 17, 2015|access-date=December 14, 2016}}</ref>
Broadcaster [[Sean Stone]] compared the mystery over Devore's fate to that of President [[John F. Kennedy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/shows/watching-the-hawks/420369-hollywood-films-politics-military/|title=Hollywood, D.C. – Part 1 (E672)|website=RT International|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-10}}</ref>
